  <brief_title>The Glycemic Effect of Taking a Supplementation of Orange Juice With Fibers</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Tel-Aviv Sourasky Medical Center</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Tel-Aviv Sourasky Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this study is to investigate the glycemic effect of supplementation Fibers in
      orange juice.

      This will be a double-blind parallel controlled study. Each subject will serve as his own
      control.

      Study population will include 10 subjects. The subjects will be randomly assigned to receive
      one of two juices in occasion, in two visits. Each drink will be containing orange juice
      with\without fibers.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
